A lot of twists and deaths. I feel like:
The Last Jedi was alright.

For an Empire Strikes Back remake. With hour-long subplots that LITERALLY go nowhere. And no character development. And less imagination than the prequels. And more plot-holes than a 90's B-movie.

Ok so the entire thing was an absolute cluster-fuck who's entire success hinges on nostalgia for movies that people don't even remember anymore.

I miss George- wait no. I miss Paul Hirsch\, Marcia Lucas\, and Richard Chew.
